OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FEnd living costs charge for
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fwrongfully convicted - MP  
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A senior Conservative MP has urged     
OL,6, ministers to change prison compensation
OL,7, rules after it emerged a man who       
OL,8, wrongly spent 17 years in jail may have
OL,9, money deducted from his payout.        
OL,11,FAndrew Malkinson, 57, was cleared of a 
OL,12,Frape he did not commit. He called the  
OL,13,Fcurrent rules "kind of sick".          
OL,15,FUnder existing rules, savings made on  
OL,16,Fliving costs while in prison can be    
OL,17,Fdeducted from compensation.            
OL,19,FSir Bob Neill said: "Any fair-minded   
OL,20,Fperson thinks this is just wrong."     
